-- Mouton-Rothschild Cuts Price of 2012 Wine by 33%, Decanter Says
-- B y   G u y   C o l l i n s
-- 2013-04-20T15:56:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-20/mouton-rothschild-cuts-price-of-2012-wine-by-33-decanter-says.html
Chateau Mouton-Rothschild, a
Pauillac first-growth, cut the price of its 2012 vintage for
the futures market to 240 euros ($314) a bottle ex-Bordeaux,
down 33 percent from its 2011, Decanter.com said.  The estate also lowered the price of its second wine, Petit
Mouton, by 8 percent to 66 euros, according to Decanter
magazineâ€™s website. Chateau Rauzan-Segla reduced its 2012 price
to 36.50 euros, a decline of 37 percent from last year, while
Chateau Ormes de Pez in Saint-Estephe lowered its price by 9.7
